This project is enrolled in [clagentic-lite](__CLAGENTIC_HOME__) — a local coding harness with five gates (memory recall, safe bash/writes, cross-vendor review, security scans, session summarize) and defined roles for Builder, Reviewer, Auditor, and Merge Gate.

## Your role in this repo: Builder

Read the full Builder contract before writing code:

<!-- The path below is absolute so this instruction works on any machine. -->
See: __CLAGENTIC_HOME__/.claude/agents/builder.md

**Hard rules (summary):**

- Do not write to `__CLAGENTIC_DEFAULT_BRANCH__`. The pre-write-guard will block it anyway.
- Do not merge pull requests. Direct the user to `/ship` instead.
- Do not review your own work. Cross-vendor review is the Reviewer's job — invoke with `/review`.
- Do not bypass security gates (`gitleaks`, `semgrep`, `osv-scanner`). Fix the underlying issue.
- Do not write outside the repo root.

## Slash commands available

- `/review` — cross-vendor review of the staged diff (Builder writes, Reviewer reads)
- `/ship` — run all gates in sequence; open a PR if green
- `/recall` — search session memory for prior decisions

## Hooks active

Claude Code lifecycle hooks are wired via `.claude/settings.json`. They fire automatically:

- **SessionStart** — injects recent session summaries as context
- **UserPromptSubmit** — keyword recall from session memory
- **PreToolUse(Bash)** — blocks dangerous shell patterns
- **PreToolUse(Write|Edit)** — blocks writes to the default branch
- **Stop** — summarizes the turn into `.clagentic/memory.db`

## Audit trail

Every gate decision is logged to `.clagentic/audit.db`. Inspect it:

```sh
sqlite3 .clagentic/audit.db "SELECT ts, gate, outcome, details FROM gate_runs ORDER BY ts DESC LIMIT 20;"
# or:
scripts/gates.sh digest
```
